onRevisions/66768"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EStruvite stones are a type of urinary tract calculi that form in the presence of urinary tract infections.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the radiological appearance of struvite stones?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Small and radiolucent","Spiculated and translucent","Staghorn-shaped and radiopaque","Round and smooth","Triangular and laminated"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EStruvite stones, also known as magnesium ammonium phosphate stones, have distinctive characteristics:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStaghorn-shaped and radiopaque\u003C/strong\u003E appearance due to their mineral composition and tendency to conform to the shape of the renal pelvis and calyces (Image)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmall and radiolucent\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as struvite stones are typically large and visible on X-ray\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERound and smooth\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as these stones have an irregular branching pattern\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpiculated and translucent\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as struvite stones are radiopaque and not spiculated\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETriangular and laminated\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as these stones follow the collecting system\u0027s shape\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStruvite stones form in alkaline urine when urease-producing bacteria like \u003Cem\u003EProteus\u003C/em\u003E, \u003Cem\u003EKlebsiella\u003C/em\u003E, or \u003Cem\u003EPseudomonas\u003C/em\u003E species are present. The urease enzyme splits urea into ammonia, creating an alkaline environment that promotes stone formation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Struvite (magnesium ammonium phosphate) stones appear staghorn-shaped and are associated with urease-producing bacterial infections.","Struvite stones are radiopaque on X-ray imaging due to their mineral content."],"references":["Khan SR, Pearle MS, Robertson WG, Gambaro G, Canales BK, Doizi S, Traxer O, Tiselius HG. Kidney stones. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2016 Feb 25;2:16008. doi: 10.1038/nrdp.2016.8. PMID: 27188687; PMCID: PMC5685519","Leslie SW, Sajjad H, Murphy PB. Renal Calculi, Nephrolithiasis. [Updated 2024 Apr 20]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK442014/","stroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Koeppen, B. M., \u0026 Stanton, B. A. (2018). Renal Physiology E-Book: Renal Physiology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences. Fontenelle LF, Sarti TD. Kidney Stones: Treatment and Prevention. Am Fam Physician. 2019 Apr 15;99(8):490-496. PMID: 30990297","Peerapen P, Thongboonkerd V. Kidney Stone Prevention. Adv Nutr. 2023 May;14(3):555-569. doi: 10.1016/j.advnut.2023.03.002. Epub 2023 Mar 9. PMID: 36906146; PMCID: PMC10201681"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52222"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15200"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21280"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21280","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21280"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/pRHKFNs9weVZiP29wLTqSJAfuFW5V1.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/pRHKFNs9weVZiP29wLTqSJAfuFW5V1.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":411,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52222","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52222"},"attributes"